        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/c4cdca/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-26T19:46:45.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://a-matter-of-taste.com/en/event/Napa2019\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://a-matter-of-taste.com/en/event/Napa2019</a></p>\n<p>Anybody going? Anybody go to the one last year? Tickets are pricey, but the lineup looks strong:</p>\n<p>Also on deck is the Grand Walkabout Tasting, featuring over 200 outstanding wines from around the globe, each rated 93 points or higher by Robert Parker Wine Advocate. Highlights from the Grand Walkabout Tasting include: Arkenstone, AXR Winery, B Cellars, Bevan Cellars, Carter Cellars, Catena Zapata, Cayuse, Chambers Rosewood Vineyards, Ch\u00e2teau Haut-Bailly, Continuum, Domaines Lupier, Dominus, Duemani, Fattoria le Pupille, Graham, Hall Winery, Harbison Estate Wines, Horsepower, Kapcs\u00e1ndy Family Winery, Lail Vineyards, Larkmead Vineyards, Leeuwin Estate, Morlet Family Vineyards, Ovid Winery, Patria, Poggio Al Tesoro, Quintessa, Sanguis, Schrader Cellars, Sinegal Estate, Sloan Estate, The Debate, TOR, Torbreck, Turley Wine Cellars and many more.</p>",
